==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Septicaemia
<hw>Sep`ti*cae"mi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <?/<?/<?/ putrefactive + <?/<?/<?/ blood.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A poisoned condition of the blood produced by the absorption into
it of septic or putrescent material; blood poisoning. It is marked by
chills, fever, prostration, and inflammation of the different serous
membranes and of the lungs, kidneys, and other organs.</def> <-- Now
septicemia. A condition caused by bacterial infection, the effects being
mediated by the release of toxins by bacteria, within the circulation.
(local infection is sepsis) Also septemia, septic fever, hematosepsis,
sapremia -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Septically</ent>⟦br⟧
